text: The Sheridan Main Street Historic District, in Sheridan, Wyoming, is a historic district which was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1982. It includes both sides of several blocks of Main Street, from Burkitt Street to Mandel Street, an area including the oldest portion of the historic core of Sheridan, dating back to 1882.
